HEADWORD: Nur
<hw>Nur</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. <er>Knur</er>.]</ety>
<def>A hard knot in wood; also, a hard knob of wood used by boys in
playing hockey.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I think I'm as hard as a <qex>nur</qex>, and as tough as
whitleather.</q> <rj><qau>W. Howitt.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nuragh</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Nuraghe</ent>⟦br⟧
